{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0155ykzhzv5XbHMGSFRZzmky","type":"tool_result","content":"total 0\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 oystein oystein 4096 Feb  6 15:50 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 oystein oystein 4096 Feb  6 16:29 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 oystein oystein   34 Feb  6 15:50 __init__.py\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 oystein oystein 4096 Feb  6 16:28 kernels\n-rw-r--r-- 1 oystein oystein   35 Feb  6 15:50 simulation.py","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HzCrD7VaHQYVr5M6WW352S","session_id":"3242128b-3d9b-48b8-8cfa-8a003d4cdd82","uuid":"22321bc2-e203-4f36-92ff-b85ba9577be3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YKEvmxsaTbsX3yS7t7Pjvk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it! Here is the poly6 kernel implementation from the SPHSimLib directory:\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/SPHSimLib/K_SPH_Kernels_poly6.inl`\n\n**Poly6 Kernel Formula Code:**\n\nThe implementation consists of a `Wpoly6` class with the following formulas:\n\n1. **Kernel Constant:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Kernel_Constant(float smoothing_length)\n{\n    return 315.0f / (64.0f * M_PI * pow(smoothing_length, 9.0f) );\n}\n```\n\n2. **Kernel Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Kernel_Variable(float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen_sq)\n{\n    float hsq_rlensq = smoothing_length_pow2 - rlen_sq;\n    return hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq;\t\n}\n```\n\n3. **Gradient Constant:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Gradient_Constant(float smoothing_length)\n{\n    return -945.0f / (32.0f * M_PI * pow(smoothing_length, 9.0f) );\n}\n```\n\n4. **Gradient Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Gradient_Variable(float smoothing_length, float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen)\n{\n    float hsq_rlensq = smoothing_length_pow2 - (rlen*rlen);\n    return hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq;\t\n}\n```\n\n5. **Laplace Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Laplace_Variable(float smoothing_length, float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen)\n{\n    float rlen_sq = rlen*rlen;\n    float part1 = smoothing_length_pow2 - rlen_sq;\n    float part2 = 3.0f*smoothing_length_pow2 - 7.0f*rlen_sq;\n    return part1 * part2;\t\n}\n```\n\nThe poly6 kernel is the standard smooth particle hydrodynamics poly6 kernel function used for SPH simulations, with constant coefficients and polynomial variable terms computed from the smoothing length and distance vector."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abfde9f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39887\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 8594</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3242128b-3d9b-48b8-8cfa-8a003d4cdd82","uuid":"1e4c8f7e-b587-434e-9ef2-cf44aae79a76","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for poly6 kernel implementation in the SPHSimLib directory. Look for files containing \"poly6\" or \"K_SPH_Kernels_poly6\". Read the relevant file(s) and return the poly6 kernel formula code.","agentId":"abfde9f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it! Here is the poly6 kernel implementation from the SPHSimLib directory:\n\n**File:** `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/SPHSimLib/K_SPH_Kernels_poly6.inl`\n\n**Poly6 Kernel Formula Code:**\n\nThe implementation consists of a `Wpoly6` class with the following formulas:\n\n1. **Kernel Constant:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Kernel_Constant(float smoothing_length)\n{\n    return 315.0f / (64.0f * M_PI * pow(smoothing_length, 9.0f) );\n}\n```\n\n2. **Kernel Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Kernel_Variable(float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen_sq)\n{\n    float hsq_rlensq = smoothing_length_pow2 - rlen_sq;\n    return hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq;\t\n}\n```\n\n3. **Gradient Constant:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Gradient_Constant(float smoothing_length)\n{\n    return -945.0f / (32.0f * M_PI * pow(smoothing_length, 9.0f) );\n}\n```\n\n4. **Gradient Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Gradient_Variable(float smoothing_length, float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen)\n{\n    float hsq_rlensq = smoothing_length_pow2 - (rlen*rlen);\n    return hsq_rlensq * hsq_rlensq;\t\n}\n```\n\n5. **Laplace Variable:**\n```cuda\nstatic __device__ __host__ float Laplace_Variable(float smoothing_length, float smoothing_length_pow2, float3 r, float rlen)\n{\n    float rlen_sq = rlen*rlen;\n    float part1 = smoothing_length_pow2 - rlen_sq;\n    float part2 = 3.0f*smoothing_length_pow2 - 7.0f*rlen_sq;\n    return part1 * part2;\t\n}\n```\n\nThe poly6 kernel is the standard smooth particle hydrodynamics poly6 kernel function used for SPH simulations, with constant coefficients and polynomial variable terms computed from the smoothing length and distance vector."}],"totalDurationMs":8594,"totalTokens":39887,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1530,"cache_read_input_tokens":37733,"output_tokens":619,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1530,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0}}}}
