{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KVAhZNbxgK2WWBc7xSBDja","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## US-011 - Step1 density kernel with neighbor iteration\n\n### Files created:\n- **`fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step1.cu`** -- K_Step1 CUDA kernel with:\n  - Inline 27-cell (3x3x3) neighbor iteration using cell_start/cell_end tables\n  - Per-particle mass `m_j` (not constant) for multi-material support\n  - Poly6 kernel: `density_sum += m_j * (h_sq - r_sq)^3`\n  - Squared distance cutoff (`r_sq <= h_sq`) to avoid sqrt\n  - `__ldg()` for read-only cache loads of neighbor positions and masses\n  - Self-contribution included (j==i NOT skipped)\n  - Final density clamped to `max(1.0, poly6_coeff * density_sum)`\n  - Uses shared constant memory from common.cuh (`c_grid`, `c_sim`, `c_precalc`)\n\n- **`fallingsand3d/step1.py`** -- Python wrapper with:\n  - SimParams and PrecalcParams numpy dtypes matching common.cuh structs\n  - Builder functions for sim/precalc params\n  - CuPy RawModule compilation with `--use_fast_math`\n  - Constant memory upload functions\n  - `compute_step1()` launch wrapper, block size 128\n\n- **`fallingsand3d/test_step1.py`** -- 11 integration tests, all passing:\n  - Single isolated particle: rho = mass * poly6_coeff * h^6 (exact match)\n  - Uniform field: interior density within 0.98% of rho0=1000\n  - Per-particle mass produces different densities\n  - Density clamped >= 1.0\n  - 500K particles: no errors, all finite\n\nCommitted as `2054e77`.\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":400,"cache_read_input_tokens":101432,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":400},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"se